	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Misc. NES-like graphics</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Rahsennor wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">How do you do it? Any advice for aspiring pixel artists?</div>NES specifically: use lots of black shadows to join different attributes and boost contrast, all the best looking NES games make heavy use of black, experiment with different colour combinations, I mostly just stumble on the stuff that works through trial and error.<br />Pixel art generally: have other things to do, so pixeling makes for good procrastination, spend countless hours ogling at screenshots and maps, practice for a quarter of a century.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


